text:
High school volleyball district tournament schedules: Playoff drive starts Monday 
By The Times-Union Sat, Oct 17, 2015 @ 3:13 am Photos Gary McCullough/For the Times-Union St. Johns Country Day's Madison Dill (jumping) and Brooke Arnett have the Spartans seeded No. 1 in their district. A glance at high school volleyball district tournament schedules for teams on the First Coast. Tournaments begin Monday, Oct. 19. District 1-8A at Flagler Palm Coast Teams (by seed): Spruce Creek, DeLand, Mandarin, Ocala West Port, Sandalwood, Flagler Palm Coast Schedule: Tuesday, West Port vs. Sandalwood, 5:30; Mandarin vs. FPC, 6:30; Wednesday, Spruce Creek vs. West Port-Sandalwood winner, 5:30; DeLand vs. Mandarin-FPC winner, 6:30; Thursday, championship, 6:30 Teams (by seed): Fletcher, Atlantic Coast, First Coast, Lee Schedule: Tuesday, First Coast vs. Atlantic Coast, 5:30; Fletcher vs. Lee, 6:30; Thursday, championship, 6 District 4-7A at Bartram Trail Teams (by seed): Fleming Island, Creekside, Bartram Trail, Gainesville Buchholz, Oakleaf. Schedule: Monday, Oakleaf at Buchholz, 6 p.m.; Tuesday, Creekside vs. Bartram, 5:30; Fleming vs. Oakleaf/Buchholz winner, 7; Thursday, championship, 6:30 District 3-6A at Middleburg Teams (by seed): Middleburg, St. Augustine, Nease, Englewood, White Schedule: Monday, Englewood vs. White, 7; Tuesday, St. Augustine vs. Nease, 5; Middleburg vs. Englewood-White winner, 7; Thursday, championship, 7 District 4-6A at Gainesville Teams (by seed): Ocala Forest, Ocala Vanguard, Gainesville, Lake Weir, Columbia Schedule: Monday, Columbia vs. Lake Weir, 7; Wednesday, Forest vs. Columbia-Lake Weir winner, 5; Vanguard vs. Gainesville, 7; Friday, championship, 7 District 3-5A at Paxon Teams (by seed): Bishop Kenny, Yulee, Stanton, Paxon, Parker, Ribault. Schedule: Monday, Stanton vs. Ribault, 5:30; Paxon vs. Parker, 7; Tuesday, Yulee vs. Stanton-Ribault winner, 5:30; Kenny vs. Paxon-Parker winner, 7; Thursday, championship, 6:30 Teams (by seed): Ridgeview, Orange Park, Baker County, Wolfson, Westside. Schedule: Tuesday, Orange Park vs. Baker, 5; Ridgeview vs. Wolfson, 7; Thursday, championship, 7 Note: By coach vote, Westside will not participate in the tournament Teams (by seed): Ponte Vedra, Clay, Menendez, Palatka. Schedule: Tuesday, Ponte Vedra vs. Palatka, 6; Clay vs. Menendez, 7:30; Thursday, championship, 6:30 District 3-4A at Episcopal Teams (by seed): Bolles, Episcopal, Fernandina Beach, West Nassau, Duval Charter, Raines, Jackson. Schedule: Monday, West Nassau vs. Duval Charter, 4; Episcopal vs. Jackson, 5:30; Fernandina vs. Raines, 7; Tuesday, Bolles vs. West Nassau-Duval Charter winner, 5; Episcopal-Jackson winner vs. Fernandina-Raines winner, 6:30; Thursday, championship, 6 Teams (by seed): Keystone Heights, Interlachem, Bradford Schedule: Tuesday, Bradford vs. Interlachen, 6; Thursday, championship, Keystone vs. Bradford-Interlachen winner, 6 District 2-3A at Providence Teams (by seed): St. Johns Country Day, Providence, University Christian, Trinity Christian, Bishop Snyder, Florida Deaf. Schedule: Monday, Trinity vs. Snyder, 5:30; Providence vs. UC, 7:30; Tuesday, St. Johns vs. Trinity-Snyder winner, 5:30; Providence vs. UC-Florida Deaf winner, 7:30; Thursday, championship, 7 District 3-3A at Gainesville Oak Hall Teams (by seed): P.K. Yonge, St. Francis, Oak Hall, St. Joseph. Schedule: Tuesday, St. Joseph vs. P.K. Yonge, 5; Oak Hall vs. St. Francis, 7; Thursday, championship, 7 District 2-2A at Christ’s Church Teams (by seed): Seacoast, Christ’s Church, Harvest, Parsons Christian. Schedule: Tuesday, Parsons vs. Seacoast, 5:30; Harvest vs. Christ’s Church, 7; Thursday, championship, 7 District 3-2A at Jenkins Middle School, Palatka Teams (by seed): Cornerstone, Eagle’s View, First Coast Christian, Peniel, Beacon of Hope. Schedule: Monday, Peniel vs. Beacon, 6; Tuesday, Eagle’s View vs. First Coast Christian, 5:30; Cornerstone vs. Beacon-Peniel winner, 7; Thursday, championship, 7 District 6-1A at Hilliard Teams (by seed): Union County, Baldwin, Hilliard, Fort White, Hawthorne. 
Schedule: Monday, Fort White vs. Hawthorne, 6; Tuesday, Union vs. Fort White-Hawthorne winner, 6; Hilliard vs. Baldwin, 7:30; Thursday, championship, 7:30
